'''Bijoy Sankar Barman''' is an [[Assamese language|Assamese]] writer. He has been awarded with [[Yuva Puraskar]] by [[Sahitya Akademi]].<ref name="TOI">{{cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/Assamese-poet-first-to-find-Estonian-audience/articleshow/54473915.cms | title=Assamese poet first to find Estonian audience | date=23 September 2016 | newspaper=The Times of India | first=Gaurav | last=Das | accessdate=19 July 2018 }}</ref>

==Works==
* He has compiled 32 poems in assamese language, which was then translated by Margus Lattik to [[Estonian language]] as 'Pisarateoja Ketetong'.<ref name="TOI"/>
* He was the first one to translate the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] classic [[Kuruntokai]] to [[Assamese language]]. It was named as 'Kurundoheir Kabita' in Assamese.<ref name="TOI"/>
* Ashokashtami (Won Yuva Puraskar award for this work)

==Awards==
* Sahitya Akademi's Yuva Purashkar (2013)

