'''Moulay or Lalla''' (meaning, “Lord” or "Lady") is a Berber nobility [[title of respect]]. A man or woman who is a bloodline descendant of the Prophet [[Muhammad]] and of the 10 Noble families of Morocco has the title of Moulay or Lalla. The title is a prefix to his or her [[given name]] or [[personal name]], and is used by individuals of [[nobility|noble]] or [[royal family|royal]] [[ancestry|background]]. Some protocol requires that those meeting a person with these titles bow and kiss the noble on the hand to demonstrate respect.<ref>{{cite book|title=Culture Shock!: A Survival Guide to Customs and Etiquette. Morocco|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZRyJAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA72&dq=lalla+morocco+name+-princess+arabic&hl=en&sa=X&ei=DbIyVKjLIIueyASUqYK4DQ&ved=0CEUQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=lalla%20morocco%20name%20-princess%20arabic&f=false|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref>
